## 📌 Prompt Text (v1.1 — current)

```
You are a colour key artist at a 2D animation studio working on The Adventures of Tintin.

Using ONLY the layout brief and location brief provided below, generate a structured colour key brief that will guide the background artist in applying colour, lighting and mood to their approved layout sketch.

Do not suggest colour or lighting directions that are not supported by the briefs provided.

Location brief: [LOCATION_BRIEF]
Layout brief: [P04_OUTPUT]

Required sections:
1. Light source & direction
   - Primary light source (sun / artificial / ambient)
   - Direction (top-down / side / back-lit / diffused)
   - Time of day confirmation

2. Colour key zones
   - Sky/background zone: base colour and mood
   - Midground zone: dominant colour and tone
   - Foreground zone: shadow and separation colour
   - Accent colours: 2–3 colours that draw the eye

3. Lighting mood
   - Choose one: flat / soft ambient / golden hour / 
     overcast / night — justify against brief
   - Note any lighting that conflicts with ligne claire 
     flat style constraints

4. Shadow treatment
   - Shadow presence: none / minimal / moderate
   - Shadow edge: hard / soft — justify against 
     ligne claire style constraints
   - Shadow colour: specify, do not use black

5. Mood & emotional tone
   - One sentence: what should the audience feel 
     when this background is on screen?
   - Key colour temperature: warm / cool / neutral

6. Colour consistency notes
   - Flag any colour decisions that must be matched 
     across other backgrounds in the same scene or 
     time of day

**Placeholders to fill:**

| Placeholder | Source | Example |
|-------------|--------|---------|
| `[LOCATION_BRIEF]` | Single location from P02 approved output | "Street Market — Scene 1, Day, High complexity, busy open-air European market"|
| `[P04_OUTPUT]` | Approved layout brief from P04 | Full P04 layout brief for the same location |
